description: HDFC Bank’s Arvind Kapil, with 25 years at the bank, is set to become MD & CEO of Poonawalla Fincorp. Last year, he took over HDFC's housing finance business post-merger. Poonawalla Fincorp, in a statement to stock exchanges, said that Kapil will join the company on June 24, subject to approvals. Shares of Poonawalla Fincorp rose 1.5% after the announcement.
title: HDFC Bank’s home loan business head to lead Poonawalla Fincorp

description: Delhi CM Kejriwal missed multiple ED summonses related to bribery allegations by AAP in the Delhi Jal Board case. In the DJB case, ED had claimed that bribes were received by AAP functionaries and used by the party for elections. AAP accused the Centre of obstructing the election campaign. Kejriwal faces criticism from BJP.
title: Kejriwal once again skips ED questioning, now in DJB case

description: Tata Sons is aiming to raise around Rs 9,362 crore ($1.1 billion) by selling shares of its lucrative unit Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) on Tuesday. This move is part of Tata Sons' efforts to lower its debt burden. The company is restructuring its balance sheet to avoid mandatory public listing under RBI's 'upper layer' NBFC regulations. These regulations require companies to adhere to strict guidelines, including a mandatory listing within three years of notification.
title: Tata Sons looks to sell Rs 9,000 crore TCS shares to reduce debt

description: Enforcement Directorate implicates K Kavitha, linking Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal and state's former minister Manish Sisodia in a liquor policy scam. AAP denies allegations, citing a lack of evidence and political bias. ED claims obstruction during searches, revealing significant 'proceeds of crime' in the excise case.
title: Kavitha plotted with Kejriwal, Sisodia, involved in Rs 100 crore payoff, says ED
Drunk cop opens fire & kills govt teacher, held

description: A day after gangster Rana Mansurpur fatally shot constable Amritpal Singh during a hideout raid, he was killed in an encounter near Bhangala village on the Mukerian-Pathankot national highway in Punjab's Hoshiarpur. Tracking him through CCTV footage, the police located Mansurpur heading towards Bhangala after hitching a ride on a motorcycle.
title: Police gun down gangster who shot dead Punjab cop during raid

description: In a swift judicial process, the trial of the alleged molestation case involving a Swedish national in Bhubaneswar concluded within just three weeks. The court sentenced Kundan Mahapatra to 18 months of imprisonment on Monday, as per Debabrata Mohapatra's report. This marks the fastest trial in Odisha, where justice was served within 28 days of the crime, as confirmed by the commissionerate police.
title: After 3-week trial, 18 months’ jail for priest who molested Swede

description: Supreme Court instructed SBI to reveal electoral bond details to Election Commission by Thursday 5pm, including alphanumeric numbers. The court criticized SBI for incomplete compliance with previous orders, addressing industry associations' concerns about potential misuse of data by activist lawyers.
title: Don’t be selective, disclose full bond details: SC to SBI

description: India's fish consumption surged due to rising incomes, dietary changes, improved availability. In 15 years, fish eaters and per capita consumption increased. Different states showed varying consumption patterns. Government schemes boosted aquaculture, leading to higher domestic production.
title: More Indians are now eating fish, and a lot more of it, finds study

description: The Election Commission's stringent actions against various officials aim to ensure a level-playing field in the upcoming Lok Sabha elections, removing individuals who may pose a risk to the integrity of the electoral process. In West Bengal, the EC shunted out DGP Rajeev Kumar. This is the third time that Kuma is being dropped from poll-related duties.
title: EC orders removal of home secretaries of 6 states, WB top cop

description: The Supreme Court has granted a stay on the Orissa High Court's decision to nullify Congress MLA Mohammed Moquim's election. The HC had cancelled his election citing suppression of criminal cases against him and deemed his affidavit invalid due to lack of proper verification by the returning officer. Seeking relief, Moquim swiftly approached the SC through his advocate Mithu Jai to halt the HC's order.
title: SC stays HC order nullifying election of Odisha Congress MLA
Descendant of 19th century Sufi saint joins saffron party

description: In a significant development for Madhya Pradesh politics, Syed Jaffar, a key aide of former chief minister Kamal Nath, has switched allegiance to the BJP, expressing support for the CAA. Jaffar, 42, known for his association with Kamal Nath's son Nakul Nath, had been a vocal figure for the state Congress but recently shifted his support towards the BJP regarding the CAA issue.
title: Kamal Nath aide Syed Jaffar joins BJP, backs CAA

description: Ajit Pawar criticized by brother Shrinivas, called “nalayak manoos”. Siblings distant, Shrinivas supports Pawar in Baramati. Ajit defied uncle, took oath as deputy CM in Mumbai. Criticized for disloyalty, splitting NCP. Shrinivas raked up Ajit’s “disloyalty”, and said no one was more unfit than a person abandoning a Pawar who had given him so much only to side with others for short-term gains.
title: Ajit Pawar’s brother calls him incompetent & ungrateful, supports Sule
SC refuses to stay rebel HP Cong MLAs’ disqualification

description: R S Puram, a bustling commercial hub in Coimbatore, missed a visit from national leader L K Advani in 1998. He canceled his public meeting on Feb 14 due to serial bomb blasts. Viswanathan, who runs a car rental business in the city, was at R S Puram on Feb 14, 1998, too. He had to return disappointed that day as Advani’s meeting was cancelled.
title: PM Modi’s Coimbatore yatra, and a trip down a bitter memory lane

description: Another convict in the Bilkis Bano case has approached the Supreme Court to review its recent decision revoking the reduction of his sentence. Ramesh Rupabhai Chandana argues that the Court's ruling should not be challenged based on the severity of the crime and the public's demand for justice. He asserts that the Court made an error in overturning a previous judgment from May 13, 2022.
title: 1 more convict seeks review of Supreme Court's Bilkis order

description: The Supreme Court dismissed industry bodies' application opposing the disclosure of Electoral Bonds' alphanumeric numbers. The Court rebuffed late interventions and emphasized following proper procedures for hearings. Finding that the application was filed on Monday morning, the CJI said that the application was not before us and it is also not numbered.
title: SC junks industry bodies’ 11th-hour plea to stop EB code disclosure

description: LJP (Ram Vilas) chief Chirag Paswan, after securing five Lok Sabha seats to contest within the NDA, announced plans to campaign alongside Bihar chief minister Nitish Kumar for a potential 40-seat sweep in Bihar. Chirag's rift with Nitish Kumar led to his party split and subsequent sidelining. Nitish blamed Chirag for the sharp drop in the number of his seats and an acute sense of frustration.
title: For 400+, all allies must be on same platform amicably: Chirag Paswan

description: Union govt distances from SC Bar Association president's plea  for reconsideration of the SC’s direction on electoral bonds. Solicitor general supports SC's disclosure direction but he also flagged what he described as the unintended consequence of the verdict. Harish Salve emphasizes SBI's transparency. SC focused on enforcing directions, not PILs becoming publicity interest litigation.
title: Electoral bonds: Not tied to SC bar body president plea, says govt

description: A tragic incident unfolded in Garden Reach as a five-storey building, built illegally in a congested area, collapsed, resulting in the loss of 10 lives and injury to 17 individuals. Rescue efforts are ongoing to locate three missing persons buried under the debris. The victims, mostly from a nearby slum, included two construction labourers. Md Wasim alias Wasi, the building promoter, has been arrested and charged with various offences.
title: Under-construction Kolkata building falls on slum, 10 dead

description: In Kuno, there are not five but six new balls of fur, with Cheetah Gamini giving birth to a rare half a dozen cubs, as per Union environment minister Bhupendra Yadav. This litter exceeds the usual count of four to five cubs for cheetahs. Newborn cheetahs are hard to spot as the mother ensures a well-hidden and safe birthing spot.
title: Cheetah Gamini gave birth to ‘record’ 6 cubs: Government
Ensure no beverage is sold as ‘health drink’: NCPCR

description: The Madras high court has barred ousted AIADMK leader O Paneerselvam from using the party's official letterhead, symbol "Two Leaves," and flag. This decision comes in response to a suit and applications filed by AIADMK general secretary and former CM Edappadi K Palaniswami. Justice N Sathishkumar issued the order following a previous interim order on November 7, 2023, which restrained Paneerselvam from utilizing the party's letterhead, symbol, and flag.
title: Madras HC restrains OPS from using ADMK symbol, flag, letterhead

description: Ashok Chavan, a BJP Rajya Sabha member, dismissed Rahul Gandhi's criticism as unfounded and irrational. "“Rahul Gandhi did not mention my name. If he is referring to me, then I will describe his remarks as baseless and illogical. Let me make it clear, before joining BJP I did not meet Congress leader Sonia Gandhi in New Delhi," Chavan said.
title: Rahul Gandhi lying, says Ashok Chavan reacting to ‘weeping’ claim

description: India and US strengthen strategic ties through Tiger Triumph exercise and INDUS-X summit. Emphasis on technology collaboration, aero-engines, ISR systems, smart munitions, Stryker vehicles, USS Somerset, Army troops, landing crafts, IAF aircraft, and humanitarian aid.
title: Amid military drill, Rajnath & Austin discuss boosting ties

description: BJP finalized the distribution of Lok Sabha seats in Bihar on Monday. The party will contest 17 seats, while Nitish Kumar's JD(U) will vie for 16. The remaining five seats were allocated to Chirag Paswan's LJP faction, founded by Ram Vilas Paswan. HAM and RLM, NDA allies, secured one seat each. The LJP faction led by Pashupati Kr Paras did not receive any seats.
title: Bihar NDA seat-sharing: Chirag gets 5, uncle none

description: The Army's STEAG unit evaluates advanced technologies like AI, 5G, 6G for military use. It aims to enhance communication capabilities for a battlefield edge through tailored tech development and collaboration with academia, industry. Modern warfare makes it necessary to induct new equipment to provide seamless communication support to units and formations during operations.
title: Eye on future wars, Army raises elite tech unit

description: Former chief minister and Bangalore North MP, DV Sadananda Gowda, expressed his disappointment after not being given a ticket by the BJP for the upcoming Lok Sabha elections, joining the growing discontent within the party. Following in the footsteps of senior party member KS Eshwarappa, Gowda, 71, announced that he will reveal his next steps on Tuesday.
title: Got Congress invite: Karnataka ex-CM as wave of dissent hits BJP

description: In Bengaluru, a businessman playing Hanuman Chalisa was assaulted by a group accusing him of disturbing prayers with loud music. Three arrested, two absconding. Dispute over music near the store entrance, alleged fabricated prayer disturbance. Investigators stated that the claim was just an excused to pick up the fight. BJP blamed the Congress government’s “appeasement politics” for such incidents.
title: B'luru shopowner assaulted for playing Hanuman Chalisa, 3 held

description: A day after Rahul Gandhi criticized PM Modi in Mumbai, the Prime Minister responded at a rally in Telangana's Jagtial, emphasizing the importance of protecting "Shakti" on Indian soil. He urged the crowd to give a strong response to the opposition alliance for discussing the destruction of "Shiv Shakti," recently celebrated for the success of the Chandrayaan lunar mission.
title: PM Modi invokes ‘Shakti’ as divinity, slams Rahul Gandhi’s remark

description: In an unusual turn of events, brothers Vikas and Vivek Sahay have both taken up the role of director general of police (DGP) in different states. Vikas Sahay is currently serving as the DGP of Gujarat, while Vivek Sahay was appointed as the DGP of West Bengal by the state government on Monday. Their youngest brother, Vikram Sahay, works as an Indian Revenue Service officer in Delhi.
title: Uniform order: Two states, two brothers, both DGPs

description: Indian Navy's swift 40-hour operation, with PM Modi's support, rescued the hijacked MV Ruen from Somali pirates, ensuring the safety of seven Bulgarians. The operation showcased international cooperation and the Navy's commitment to combating piracy. As India rescued Bulgarian ship and its citizens, President expressed gratitude to PM Modi and Indian navy.
title: Bulgaria prez thanks PM for Indian Navy’s anti-piracy operation

description: n a recent speech in Mumbai, Rahul Gandhi accused PM Narendra Modi of distorting his words, claiming that Modi symbolizes the forces of "evil, corruption, and lies" as the "mask" and "slave". Rahul clarified that the "shakti" referred to is the power that has ensnared "the entire constitutional structure of the country", which the opposition is battling.
title: Didn’t talk of religious shakti but one of evil, clarifies Rahul

description: Jammu and Kashmir SIA filed chargesheet against Zaheed Khoja and Zameer Lone for narco-terror financing under the NDPS Act, UAPA. Lone, a LeT terrorist in Pakistan/PoK, conspired to spread communal disharmony. Both plotted criminal conspiracy to raise funds by unlawful practices to financially support the terror, including setting ablaze govt buildings and residential houses of minority communities.
title: Narco-terror financing: J&K SIA files chargesheet against two

description: Omar Abdullah affirms PAGD cohesion despite NC's separate LS strategy. The alliance, including NC, PDP, CPI(M), and Awami National Conference, prepares for the Valley's LS seats. Omar criticises the Centre's interference in Jammu and Kashmir elections. Earlier, Omar said that the NC would contest election on all the three Lok Sabha seats in the valley, leaving the J&K to INDIA bloc.
title: Omar says PAGD intact, signals Lok Sabha seat rethink

description: President of the Republic of Bulgaria, Rumen Radev, extended his gratitude to the Indian Navy on Monday for successfully rescuing its 7 crew members that were being held hostage by pirates aboard a hijacked Bulgarian ship. In a post on X, the President conferred his sincere gratitude to PM Modi for the brave action of the Navy rescuing the hijacked Bulgarian ship.
title: Bulgarian President thanks India for rescuing hijacked ship MV Ruen

description: US President Joe Biden and Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu discussed Gaza food crisis, war conduct, amid Schumer's criticism and calls for Israeli elections. This was the first phone call between the two leaders in over a month. White House is cautious of Netanyahu's Rafah operation without a credible plan for Palestinian safety.
title: Gaza war: Biden, Netanyahu hold first call in over a month

description: India's newest batting star Sarfaraz Khan and wicket-keeper Dhruv Jurel were inducted into Group C of BCCI's central contract with an annual retainership fee of Rs 1 crore, having fulfilled the criteria of playing three Tests in a current season.
title: Sarfaraz, Jurel get BCCI's central contracts

description: Former KKR captain Gautam Gambhir transitions to 'Team Mentor,' aiming to elevate the team's performance. He acknowledged the crucial role of Shah Rukh Khan in his career and remains determined to lead KKR to greater success. "I can assure you that whenever I leave this place (KKR), we will be in a much better position," Gambhir affirmed during a promotional event ahead of the upcoming IPL season, underscoring his commitment to KKR's progress.
title: 'I didn't make KKR successful...': Gautam Gambhir

description: Trinamool Congress MP Saket Gokhale lodged a complaint against Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Monday, accusing him of breaching the poll code by using an Indian Air Force helicopter to attend an election rally in Andhra Pradesh. Gokhale asserted that PM Modi arrived at the rally site, organised as part of BJP's election campaign, in an IAF helicopter with tail number ZP 5236.
title: TMC MP files complaint against PM Modi for poll code violation

description: Kremlin on Monday said it sees itself as being at war with the United States because of its role in the Ukraine war. "Given that de-facto the United States is a country deeply involved in the war in Ukraine. This is a country that is, in fact, at war with us," Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said.
title: 'United States is at war with us,' says Russia after Putin win

description: PMK announces alliance with BJP for Lok Sabha polls. Vadivel Ravanan shares NDA alliance details. PM Modi's event coincides with announcement. AIADMK signaled. Dr. Anbumani to possibly finalize seats with PM.
title: Lok Sabha elections: PMK ties up with BJP in Tamil Nadu

description: A recent study conducted by the Climate Central highlights an alarming trend in India's winter temperatures, indicating a potential shortening of the spring season. The acceleration in temperatures, largely attributed to human-induced climate change, poses concerns for the abrupt transition from winter to warmer temperature conditions traditionally associated with March.
title: Winter temp trends in India hint at shorter spring: Study
Indian student dies in US, initial probe rules out foul play

description: NASA's Hubble Space Telescope captures LEDA 42160, a galaxy 52 million light-years away in Virgo. Ram pressure shapes it, stripping star-forming materials but boosting star formation in other areas. NASA studies dwarf galaxies like LEDA 42160 to understand star formation triggers. Bright patches suggest active star formation regions, revealing insights into galaxy evolution.
title: 'Ram pressure can make stars': Nasa captures Virgo Galaxy cluster
Can India match China's past 8-10% growth? What Morgan Stanley says

description: DY Chandrachud reprimanded senior advocate Mathews Nedumpara after a heated exchange during a hearing on electoral bonds. "Don't shout at me," the CJI said, adding, "This is not a Hyde Park corner meeting, you are in the court." Nedumpara was questioning the SC's ruling, stating that "the entire electoral bond judgement was delivered behind the citizens back."
title: 'Don't shout at me': CJI scolds lawyer during electoral bond hearing
Will BJP's 'rotational policy' impact NDA's prospects in Bihar?

description: Mumbai Indians on Monday announced Rohit Sharma's return for the IPL season, referencing his playful 'garden' comment. After a lengthy home schedule, Rohit joins the MI camp as the franchise gears up for the upcoming season.
title: 'Garden me...': MI's unique welcome for Rohit

description: Star batter Virat Kohli has been absent from competitive cricket since the conclusion of the two T20I matches against Afghanistan in January. His absence was extended to the five-match Test series against England at home due to the birth of his son Akaay in London. Defending champions Chennai Super Kings (CSK) set to clash with RCB in a South Indian derby in IPL opener on March 22 in Chennai.
title: 'Kya baat hai yaar': Kohli happy to be back at RCB den

description: The US government's efforts to separate TikTok from its Chinese parent company ByteDance have escalated, with recent legislation passing in the House of Representatives. However, Beijing is expected to firmly reject any forced sale of the app and its valuable algorithm. Analysts describe the US actions as akin to "daylight robbery," though Beijing's response has been relatively restrained.
title: How TikTok's 'secret sauce' is straining US-China relations

description: TRAI tightens MNP rules to prevent SIM frauds, imposing 7-day porting restriction post swap. New UPC criteria introduced for transfer. Users can request porting by SMS to 1900, receiving UPC at point of sale. MNP is a facility that allows a user to move from one telecom operator to another operator – irrespective of geographical area – if he/ she is not satisfied with the services of his current operator.
title: MNP rules changed: Here's what telecom users need to know

description: The cost of Rs 50,000 imposed on APRL will be deposited with the Supreme Court Legal Aid Committee, Justice Bose said while reading out the operative portion of the judgement.
title: Adani Power: SC rejects firm's plea for over Rs 1300cr

description: Hardik Pandya replaced a highly-successful Rohit Sharma, who led the franchise to five IPL titles, as skipper ahead of the upcoming season of the IPL. Following a successful two-year stint at Gujarat Titans -- where Hardik took the side to 2 finals and winning one of them in 2022 -- the all-rounder returned to Mumbai in a high-profile trade ahead of the December 19 auction.
title: Watch: Boucher awkwardly stays mum on Rohit query

description: The NDA in Bihar announced its seat sharing agreement, with BJP contesting 17 seats and JD(U) 16. LJP, HAM, and RLP will contest 5, 1, and 1 seat respectively. The 2024 Lok Sabha elections in Bihar will be held in seven phases from April 19 to June 1. In 2019, NDA won 39 out of 40 seats while the opposition managed only one.
title: NDA seat-sharing in Bihar: BJP to contest on 17 seats, JD(U) gets 16

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi congratulated Vladimir Putin on his re-election as the President of Russia on Monday. In post on X, PM Modi "Warm congratulations to H.E. Mr. Vladimir Putin on his re-election as the President of the Russian Federation. Look forward to working together to further strengthen the time-tested Special & Privileged Strategic Partnership between India and Russia in the years to come.
title: PM Modi congratulates Russia's Putin on re-election

description: Having survived a horrific car crash in December, 2022, wicketkeeper-batter Rishabh Pant will make a comeback to competitive cricket after more than 14 months as Delhi Capitals captain after an extensive rehabilitation programme. Former Indian captain Sunil Gavaskar acknowledged that Pant's presence and his lively personality contribute significantly to the entertainment factor of the IPL.
title: 'Rishabh might find it very...' Gavaskar on Pant's comeback

description: Dadasaheb Bhagat's journey from a daily wage-earner to successful entrepreneur impressed Sharks in Shark Tank India 3. Aman Gupta invested Rs 1 crore for 10% equity in his Indian design software, while Peyush offered a conditional deal focusing on team building. He then says, 'Sir aap apne aap ko iss industry ke gunde kehte ho, aap gunde nahi baazigar ho.'
title: From office boy to Shark Tank India: Dadasaheb Bhagat's journey impresses Sharks

description: A clinical Royal Challengers Bangalore won the Women's Premier League 2024 title with an eight-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals in the final on Sunday. Batting first, DC were bowled out for 113 in 18.3 overs. RCB chased down the target of 114 with three balls to spare, much to the disappointment of the weekend crowd that turned out to support the home team.
title: RR's hilarious Jethalal post after RCB women win title
From India to Japan, how China is driving an arms race in Asia

description: China's President Xi Jinping congratulated Vladimir Putin on his re-election, emphasizing strong support from the Russian populace. Putin echoed sentiments, foreseeing enhanced Russia-China ties. Despite Western criticism, China's reluctance to condemn Russia's actions in Ukraine has bolstered Putin's stance, drawing the two nations closer as allies against the US-led West, raising global concerns.
title: China's Xi congratulates Putin on re-election, says ties will strengthen
Pak airstrikes in Afghanistan kill 8, Taliban retaliates

description: Narayana Murthy’s big gift for grandson! Four-month-old Ekagrah Rohan Murty, grandson of billionaire NR Narayana Murthy, has received a big gift of 15 lakh Infosys shares worth over Rs 240 crore from his grandfather. This gift reduces Narayana Murthy's stake to 0.36% in Infosys.
title: Narayana Murthy gifts Infy shares worth over Rs 240cr to grandson

description: A bench comprising Justices Sanjiv Khanna and Dipankar Datta issued a notice to the office of the HP assembly speaker, Kuldeep Singh Pathania, and sought its response to the plea within four weeks. The SC refused to halt the disqualification order issued by the Himachal Pradesh assembly speaker against six Congress rebels. These rebels had engaged in cross-voting during the recent Rajya Sabha polls in the state.
title: SC refuses to stay disqualification of 6 Congress MLAs from HP
Ashok Chavan responds to Rahul's 'crying leader' remark

description: India, led by IT minister Vaishnaw, aims to be a top semiconductor producer in 5 years, leveraging talent pool and global partnerships. Strong government-industry collaboration drives the country's ambition in the semiconductor space. As per Vaishnaw, India sees itself as a “trusted value chain partner” for electronic device manufacturers, industrial and defence electronics, power electronics.
title: Why IT minister not worried about investors' concern on semiconductor manufacturing

description: Mercedes integrates Apptronik's Apollo humanoid robots in factories for various tasks, with potential use cases in logistics. Apollo, modular with LED communication features, was announced in August 2023. Jorg Burzer explores robotics' impact on automotive manufacturing.
title: Meet Apollo, the robot that will work at Mercedes-Benz factories

description: City police arrested three youths in Bengaluru for attempted murder after they stabbed a shop owner during evening prayers. Investigations are ongoing, and the accused are in custody, yet to be identified.
title: B'luru shop owner stabbed for 'playing bhajan' on loudspeaker

description: Ahead of IPL, Hardik Pandya expressed joy in leading Mumbai Indians, aiming to excel as an all-rounder. Boucher praised Thushara & Malinga's camaraderie. IPL 2024 begins on March 22, with Mumbai Indians facing Gujarat Titans on March 24. Pandya had made his IPL debut with Mumbai Indians in 2015 and won four titles with the side before joining Gujarat Titans in 2022.
title: I'll be carrying forward what Rohit Sharma started for MI: Pandya

description: RPPL organized the Indian Racing Festival in Srinagar, with discussions on India's motorsports future. No official updates on F1's return since 2013, but potential for a comeback, boosting tourism in the region.
title: PM Modi lauds motorsports: F1 return on Dal Lake roads possible?

description: TDS rates for FY 2024-25: When making a payment subject to TDS, the payer must deduct a specified percentage of the amount paid. The recipient then receives a TDS certificate from the deductor, indicating the amount deducted.
title: Tax Deducted at Source guide: TDS rates for various incomes in FY25
Alienware Aurora R16 review: Conservative, but powerful
LS polls: EC orders removal of home secretaries in 6 states, West Bengal DGP

description: Veteran India off-spinner Ravichandra Ashwin sent out a message to his former IPL employers Chennai Super Kings on microblogging website 'X' seeking help ahead of the 17th Indian Premier League (IPL) season, which begins on March 22 with the match between CSK and Royal Challengers Bangalore on March 22 in Chennai.
title: Ashwin asks for 'help' from CSK ahead of IPL 2024

description: Nasa tested deep-space communication by beaming a cat video 19 million miles away, showcasing the importance of innovative technology like DTN. This experiment with Taters the cat highlights advancements in space communication for future missions.
title: Why Nasa beamed a cat video 19 million miles into deep space

description: PM Modi criticizes Rahul Gandhi's 'Shakti' remark, emphasizing devotion to all women as 'Shakti'. Election battle highlighted with increasing BJP wave in Telangana. Slams Congress, INDIA bloc, and BRS for corruption and anti-Hindu sentiments.
title: PM Modi hits out at Rahul Gandhi over his 'Shakti' remark

description: YouTube Music introduces 'Song' & 'Voice' tabs with AI search for Android users. 'Hum-to-search' feature allows playing, singing, or humming. Upcoming 'Trim Silence' option for podcasts to skip silent periods and shorten runtimes.
title: You can now ‘hum-to-search’ songs on YouTube Music: Here’s how
Ed Sheeran's concert: Man spotted with QR code printed on T-shirt

description: Tax tips to cut your tax outgo: For a taxpayer falling in the 30% tax bracket, availing just 7-8 of the 10 perks listed below can help potentially slash the annual tax liability by over Rs 1 lakh.
title: How to cut tax outgo by over Rs 1L! Top perks you shouldn’t miss

description: Elvish Yadav, Bigg Boss OTT 2 winner, admitted to snake venom case involvement. Confessed arranging snakes, facing Wildlife Act and Narcotic Drugs Act charges, along with Bollywood singer Fazilpuria's involvement. Five accused arrested after NGO complaint.
title: Elvish Yadav admits to arranging snake venom at rave parties

description: Lucknow Super Giants' 10-km run, titled 'Run today for greener tomorrow' featured the IPL team's foreign coaching staff dancing to the famous punjabi song 'bolo tara ra ra', as the event promoted environmental awareness, fitness and receiving support from the people of Lucknow ahead of the IPL season beginning March 22.
title: Watch: IPL bhangra in Lucknow - by Jonty, Langer, Klusener

description: India run machine and former captain Virat Kohli arrived in Bengaluru ahead of the upcoming season of the Indian Premier League. India and RCB stalwart Kohli has been with the franchise since the inception of the IPL and has led the team from the front for nine years. Kohli missed India's 4-1 Test series triumph over England for personal reasons.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli joins RCB camp ahead of IPL 2024

description: Devin AI by Cognition, the first AI software engineer, excels in coding and machine learning. It develops websites, debugs autonomously, and generates ControlNet images with concealed messages, offering limited access in beta testing phase.
title: Devin AI: What is it, steps to get access and all you need to know

description: On the sides, no major changes will be made except for the newly designed 16-inch alloy wheels and at the rear too it will get minimal cosmetic changes. It will include a re-designed tailgate with a sleeker bumper and revised taillights with LEDs. Other highlights will include reflectors on bumpers, high-mounted stop lamps, shark-fin antenna and integrated spoiler.
title: Tata Punch facelift spotted testing for 1st time
RBI warns banks of increase in cyber threats: Shares action points

description: Eutelsat OneWeb has emerged as a frontrunner in the satellite broadband race in India, focusing on a B2B model with 'Ka' and 'Ku' band spectrum. It is positioning itself to lead the race in providing satellite broadband services in India, surpassing competitors like Elon Musk's Starlink and Mukesh Ambani’s Reliance Jio.
title: Sunil Mittal may steal a march over Ambani & Elon Musk; here's how

description: Travelers express concerns over Boeing 737 MAX safety, prompting a shift in flight decisions. Recent incidents have increased passenger have led to increased scrutiny of aircraft models before booking. Boeing faces scrutiny after accidents affecting the 737 MAX, impacting its reputation and prompting safety modifications.
title: Why many passengers are unwilling to flying Boeing's 737 Max

description: A Google software engineer in Bengaluru faced verbal abuse from an Uber driver, sparking a viral social media post. The driver abruptly left the engineer and his companion midway during the journey, reflecting growing concerns with ride-hailing services.
title: B'luru techie shares troubling incident of Uber experience
Apple, Google may sign biggest AI deal, bringing Gemini to iPhones

description: India builds climate-controlled bunkers at Sela Pass in Arunachal Pradesh to shelter soldiers in extreme temperatures. The bunkers, integrated into border infrastructure, feature green technologies and aim to improve troop comfort and combat readiness.
title: India building dozens of bunkers at LAC to help soldiers beat cold

description: RCB captain Smriti Mandhana struggled to hear Kohli's post-match message due to the noise. In the first innings, RCB's spin attack worked its magic to offset DC's blazing start. The onslaught was led by Sophie Molineux, but RCB's 21-year-old off-spinner Shreyanka Patil changed the game with a four-wicket haul and eliminated the tail end to limit DC to a disappointing 113.
title: 'Didn't hear anything because...': Smriti on speaking to Virat Kohli
Telangana gov Tamilisai resigns, likely to contest LS polls

description: India's $250 billion IT sector is expected to witness stagnant salaries in 2024 due to global challenges impacting company operations. Average salary appraisals are projected to range from 8.4% to 9%, with a focus on stabilizing headcounts and exploring ways to enhance gross margins.
title: Indian IT sector employees likely to see flat salary hikes

description: The Supreme Court has instructed the State Bank of India (SBI) to disclose all information regarding Electoral Bonds in its possession, including the unique alphanumeric and serial numbers of redeemed bonds. SBI's Chairman must submit an affidavit by Thursday, 5 pm, confirming that all details of the Electoral Bonds have been disclosed without withholding any information.
title: SC pulls up SBI over selective disclosure of electoral bonds data, gives March 21 deadline

description: Bishan Singh, 75, from Khandoor, died at Shambu border due to cardiac arrest. He owned one acre of land, had five brothers, and was taken to Rajpura hospital where he was declared brought dead.
title: Another protesting farmer dies at Shambhu border in Punjab

description: Uber fined Rs 20,000 by Consumer Disputes Commission for overcharging. Prashar paid Rs 1,334 for a 15-minute trip. Uber refunded Rs 975. Consumer court criticized fare discrepancy and lack of transparency in Uber's operations.
title: Man charged Rs 1,334 for 8.8km Uber ride, gets Rs 10k compensation

description: RCB's women secured victory against Delhi Capitals in the Women's Premier League final, ending a trophy drought. Shreyanka Patil's exceptional performance, despite a hairline fracture, and Sophie Molineux's impactful play were key highlights. Delhi Capitals finished runners-up for the second year in a row. RCB (115/2) chased down the target with 3 balls to spare as superstar all-rounder Ellyse Perry hit an unbeaten 35.
title: Watch: How RCB beat DC in WPL final to win maiden title

description: Seven people, including three children, died in a collision between a jeep and an overloaded tractor in Khagaria, Bihar. The accident occurred near a petrol pump in Pasraha. Injured individuals were taken to a nearby health facility.
title: 7 killed, 6 injured after vehicle collides with tractor in Bihar

description: Oracle warns Mac users of macOS 14.4 issue disrupting Java apps' functionality, affecting Java versions from Java 8 to JDK 22. Workarounds are unavailable, making it challenging to revert to a stable configuration without complete system backups.
title: Oracle is warning these Mac users not to update to latest version
Arvind Kejriwal skips ED summons in Delhi Jal Board case

description: RCB women's team's victory in WPL final sparks social media support from the past and present RCB men's team stars like Virat Kohli, Faf du Plessis, Glenn Maxwell, Chris Gayle and Yuzvendra Chahal. Key RCB players Ellyse Perry, Shreyanka Patil and Sophie Molineux shine in historic win for the franchise.
title: Virat leads congratulatory messages to RCB women's team

description: Amid swirling rumors, Han So Hee and Ryu Jun Yeol's Hawaii trip revealed lackluster demeanor. Dispatch delved into their interactions with Hyeri. Tension ensued during the trip, with Ryu Jun Yeol's heavy return to Korea.
title: Han So, Ryu Jun's tense date: Closer look at rumored romance

description: After successfully rescuing the hijacked merchant vessel Ruen and its 17-member crew, the Indian Navy is now bringing the 35 Somali pirates in its custody to India. The pirates, who had taken control of MV Ruen to use it as a 'mother pirate ship' for attacking other commercial vessels, will face prosecution under Indian laws.
title: Navy to bring 35 Somali pirates to India for prosecution

description: President Vladimir Putin won a record post-Soviet landslide in Russia's election on Sunday, cementing his already tight grip on power in a victory he said showed Moscow had been right to stand up to the West and send its troops into Ukraine. Putin, a former KGB lieutenant colonel who first rose to power in 1999, made it clear that the result should send a message to the West that its leaders will have to reckon with an emboldened Russia, whether in war or in peace, for many more years to come.
title: Putin wins Russia presidential polls, warns west of WW3

description: Train 12548 derailed near Ajmer with no casualties. Help desk established with helpline 0145-2429642. Six trains cancelled, two routes diverted.
title: Engine, 4 coaches of train derails near Ajmer, no casualties

description: Santiago Martin, top donor to political parties, established lottery empire in TN, faced legal issues, family entered politics. Known for high tax payments, involved in real estate, education, and media ventures, faced I-T scrutiny in Coimbatore.
title: Electoral bonds: Teashop to jackpot, here's how 'Lottery King' Santiago Martin played to win

description: COAI requests govt. assistance in combating telecom equipment theft, emphasizing member losses. Urges DoT action, website blocking. Theft incidents rose since Oct 2023, mainly in specific regions. Customer service quality decline highlighted.
title: Why Jio, Airtel, Vodafone want govt to block these foreign websites

description: Under-construction building collapse in Kolkata's Garden Reach triggers rescue efforts. 10 rescued; search for survivors continues. Suvendu Adhikari calls for State Disaster Management Team involvement, highlighting a critical situation for rescuers.
title: Under-construction building collapses in Kolkata, rescue operation under way

description: SpaceX is building a spy satellite network under a $1.8B NRO contract to enhance global intelligence gathering and military targeting. The system, including unacknowledged satellites, provides continuous ground imagery for US government operations. “The National Reconnaissance Office is developing the most capable, diverse, and resilient space-based intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance system the world has ever seen,” a spokesperson was quoted as saying.
title: SpaceX may be building spy satellite network for US agency

description: Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB) women, led by Smriti Mandhana, clinched their maiden WPL title by defeating Delhi Capitals. The girls in red and black, emerged victorious by eight wickets against Delhi Capitals. A strong spin attack and aggressive batting led by Lanning and Shafali secured their victory in the final.
title: RCB win maiden WPL title with an all-round display
